image.altText: A lady sitting on a porch with documents

props.synopsis: The Australian Taxation Office is owed tens of billions of dollars worth of income tax debts it once dismissed as being "uneconomical to pursue". It's been a shock for many taxpayers to now have the debts resurrected. These debts in some cases date back more than a decade and are pushing some towards bankruptcy.

title.children: Taxpayers left 'absolutely devastated' as ATO starts chasing up previously 'invisible' old tax debts

image.altText: A woman wearing a long sleeved pink and khaki top stands in the House of Representatives.

props.synopsis: How many older Australians is the government willing to squeeze to help fund a bigger and better aged care sector? And how hard is it willing to squeeze them, asks David Speers.

title.children: The government is preparing to squeeze older Australians on aged care costs — and the opposition is keeping unusually quiet

image.altText: A garbage truck with fire.

props.synopsis: Lithium-ion batteries have been responsible for more than 1,000 fires during the past year in Australia. Industry and government want regulation and action.

title.children: 'Large exothermic reaction': Exposed batteries are causing hundreds of fires

image.altText: Shane walks along carrying documents and wearing sunglasses.

props.synopsis: Former ACT director of public prosecutions Shane Drumgold is seeking to have three chapters in a report by Walter Sofronoff on the prosecution of Bruce Lehrmann redacted after a judicial review found a fair-minded observer could conclude a journalist impacted Mr Sofronoff's views.

title.children: ACT government rejects calls from former top prosecutor to partially redact report into Bruce Lehrmann's prosecution

image.altText: A gun at kids swimming lessons in Israel.

props.synopsis: Regular Israelis are taking up arms in record numbers in the wake of the October 7 attack. It's left some Palestinian citizens of Israel fearful.

title.children: At kids swimming lessons in Jerusalem, half the parents are holding massive weapons

image.altText: Clogging class

props.synopsis: A major Australian review finds exercise shouldn't just be an add-on treatment for depression and the benefits might be heightened if you've never tried a downward dog or deadlift before.

title.children: What's the best exercise to help treat depression? That answer changes if you're a man or woman

image.altText: Image of man standing on edge of the lake with oyster lease and boat behind him

props.synopsis: Water temperatures reached 29 degrees in parts of Merimbula Lake in the past week, forcing oyster farmers to close harvesting on a south coast estuary lake farmed for more than a century.

title.children: Sydney rock oyster farmers in hot water as marine heatwave leads to closure of lake

image.altText: A mine rescue vehicle on a road.

props.synopsis: Rescuers are trying to free a man, trapped by a rockfall 3 kilometres from the mine entry, 500 metres underground at the Ballarat Gold Mine.

title.children: One Victorian miner still trapped, after 27 caught in rockfall at Ballarat Gold Mine

image.altText: a man holding a child and hugging a woman

props.synopsis: Mariam Raad was arrested in January 2023 and charged with entering or remaining in an area controlled by the Islamic State group.

title.children: ISIS wife who returned to Australia expected to enter plea, sentencing set for June

image.altText: An aerial image of a car and seven people in the bush

props.synopsis: Seven people have been found alive after becoming stranded for days in Western Australia's flooded outback.

title.children: Missing group found alive after becoming stranded in WA's flood-stricken outback

image.altText: Treasurer Jim Chalmers in the corridors of Parliament House.

props.synopsis: The treasurer is set to manage the expectations of a larger surplus in a pre-budget address, warning a decline in iron ore prices and a softening labour market will impact the bottom line.

title.children: Treasurer Jim Chalmers to temper great surplus expectations in pre-budget speech

image.altText: aerial of remote hospital near water

props.synopsis: The allegations emerged after two of the unit's most senior medicos made complaints to the state's Crime and Corruption Commission seeking protection as official whistleblowers.

title.children: Whistleblowers allege medical files were lost and patient care compromised by frontline Queensland Health unit

image.altText: A woman in traditional Indian clothes looks at the camera

props.synopsis: The father of Chaithanya Madhagani, whose body was found in a wheelie bin in Victoria's south at the weekend, says he is desperate for her remains to be repatriated to India.

title.children: 'Bring back my baby': Father of slain Victorian woman wants body returned to India

image.altText: Lambie Network websites

props.synopsis: Senator Jacqui Lambie says she cannot believe the Liberals have "gone this far" in creating a website to attack her in the lead-up to the Tasmanian election.

title.children: 'Absolutely ropeable': Lambie slams Liberals for using domain name almost identical to her official party site

image.altText: Mining trucks at the entrance to an underground mine.

title.children: Why the nickel industry wants Australians to make 'greener' electric car purchases

image.altText: Leonid Volkov looks healthy on the left image but the right shows the damage to his face after an attack

props.synopsis: A hammer-wielding assailant has attacked an exiled aide of late Russian opposition leader Alexei Navalny in Lithuania — something the country blamed on Russia.

title.children: Lithuania blames Russia for hammer attack on exiled aide of Alexei Navalny

image.altText: Composite of Finnish woman with short hair wearing a wool sweater and a blonde Australian woman holding a toddler.

props.synopsis: Australia's childcare system has been described as a "ridiculous struggle" for many working families, but could a country a world away teach us how to do it right?

title.children: While Aussies beg for babysitters on Facebook, child care in Finland is guaranteed by the government

image.altText: The TikTok logo hovering over a keyboard.

props.synopsis: Members of the US Congress have voted overwhelmingly in favour of banning TikTok in America if the company isn't sold to non-Chinese owners.

image.altText: Black and white wedding photo of murder victim Kelly Wilkinson smiling.

image.altText: The outside of a Bunnings store in Darwin.

image.altText: A crowd of people walk across the street in masks, including an older couple.

props.synopsis: Australia was one of the only countries to record an increase in life expectancy from 2019 to 2021, demonstrating the "relative success" of Australia's handling of the pandemic, an infectious diseases expert says.

title.children: Global life expectancy fell by 1.6 years during the COVID-19 pandemic but Australia bucked the trend

image.altText: South Korean troops marching.

props.synopsis: Australia has long struggled to recruit as many personnel as our defence force chiefs would like. But ours isn't the only military in the Asia-Pacific region facing issues.

title.children: Why Japan's military is relaxing rules around hair length

image.altText: A man wearing a mustard shirt and a necklace looks into the camera.

props.synopsis: Eamon McCaughan attempted suicide within two years of participating in gay conversion therapy. He says a ban proposed in the NSW parliament will save lives.

title.children: Eamon attempted suicide after participating in gay conversion therapy. He says a proposed ban in NSW will save lives

image.altText: A man and his smiling wife.

props.synopsis: A Victorian survivor of abuse and sexual violence has spoken out after her former husband was sentenced over the horror she endured at his hands.

title.children: Former White Ribbon ambassador jailed for raping wife

image.altText: A composite image of George Corcoran and Cat Felmingham

props.synopsis: Sick of languishing on the public hospital waitlist for surgery, or even just an initial consultation, these Australians felt they had no choice but to take out private health cover and wait through the 12-month exclusion period.

title.children: These public health patients got sick of waiting for essential surgery and turned to the private system instead

image.altText: People mooning the Ghan.

image.altText: Man in suit outside court

image.altText: A man standing out the front of a Service SA sign.

image.altText: Leonardo DiCaprio looks offscreen and smirks while holding a drink up in character.

title.children: Leo DiCaprio's spotlight on beef industry land clearing highlights crucial data discrepancies

image.altText: A man stands in a concrete cityscape with white headphones in and a grey shirt on.

image.altText: Jimmy Cherizier

title.children: What we know about Haiti gang leader Jimmy Chérizier known as 'Barbecue'

image.altText: A man in a black hat holds a camera up for a selfie photo

props.synopsis: A pizza delivery driver who was accused of causing the deaths of two teenagers walks free from court as a Perth judge finds the evidence at his trial does not support the allegation he took his hands off the steering wheel.

title.children: Young driver found not guilty of causing deaths of teenage friends after court case thrown out

image.altText: A vertically oriented explosion is visible against a backdrop of ocean and forested mountainside.

props.synopsis: The 18-metre, four-stage solid-fuel rocket exploded seconds after lifting off just after 11:01am, leaving behind a large cloud of smoke, fire, and fragments of the rocket.

title.children: Japanese company Space One's Kairos rocket explodes just seconds after launch
